---
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="GovCompass terms of use. The rules for using this political education website, governed by South African law."
>
  <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-6">
    Terms of Use
  </h1>

  <div class="space-y-6 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
    <p>
      <strong class="text-text-primary">Last updated:</strong> June 2026
    </p>

    <p>
      These terms govern your use of GovCompass ("the site", "we", "us"), a
      political education website. By accessing or using the site, you agree to
      these terms. If you do not agree, please do not use the site. These terms
      are governed by the laws of the Republic of South Africa.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      About GovCompass
    </h2>

    <p>
      GovCompass publishes long-form educational content explaining how
      South Africa's government and governance systems work. The content is
      provided for general information and civic education purposes only.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Educational content, not professional advice
    </h2>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li>
        The content on this site is for general educational purposes and does
        not constitute legal, financial, or professional advice.
      </li>
      <li>
        While we make every effort to ensure accuracy and to cite primary
        sources, laws, budgets, and government structures change over time. We
        do not warrant that all content is complete, current, or error-free.
      </li>
      <li>
        You should verify any information against official government sources
        before relying on it for decisions, and seek qualified professional
        advice where appropriate.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Non-partisan position
    </h2>

    <p>
      GovCompass is editorially non-partisan. We do not endorse any political
      party, candidate, or campaign. Content is intended to help citizens
      understand government systems, not to advocate for a particular political
      outcome.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Acceptable use
    </h2>

    <p>When using the site, you agree not to:</p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li>
        Use the site for any unlawful purpose or in breach of South African law;
      </li>
      <li>
        Attempt to gain unauthorised access to the site, its servers, or any
        connected systems;
      </li>
      <li>
        Interfere with or disrupt the site's operation, security, or
        availability;
      </li>
      <li>
        Submit false, abusive, or spam content through any form on the site.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Intellectual property
    </h2>

    <p>
      Unless otherwise stated, the written content on GovCompass is created by us
      and protected by copyright. You are welcome to:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li>Read, share, and link to articles for non-commercial purposes;</li>
      <li>
        Quote short extracts with clear attribution to GovCompass and a link to
        the original article.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      You may not republish entire articles, sell our content, or present it as
      your own without our written permission. Government data, legislation, and
      official documents we reference remain the property of their respective
      sources.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Links to other websites
    </h2>

    <p>
      The site links to external sources, including government websites and
      primary documents. We are not responsible for the content, accuracy, or
      availability of external sites, and a link does not imply endorsement.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Email subscriptions
    </h2>

    <p>
      If you subscribe to our mailing list, we use your email address only to
      send article notifications. You can unsubscribe at any time using the link
      in any email we send. Our handling of your personal information is
      described in our
      <a
        href="/privacy"
        class="text-compass-green underline hover:text-compass-green-dark transition-colors"
        >Privacy Policy</a
      >.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Availability and changes
    </h2>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li>
        We provide the site on an "as is" and "as available" basis and do not
        guarantee uninterrupted access.
      </li>
      <li>
        We may update, change, or remove content, and may revise these terms,
        at any time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated date.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Limitation of liability
    </h2>

    <p>
      To the extent permitted by South African law, GovCompass is not liable for
      any loss or damage arising from your use of, or reliance on, the site or
      its content. Nothing in these terms excludes liability that cannot lawfully
      be excluded.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Governing law
    </h2>

    <p>
      These terms are governed by and interpreted in accordance with the laws of
      the Republic of South Africa.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Contact
    </h2>

    <p>
      Questions about these terms can be sent via our
      <a
        href="/contact"
        class="text-compass-green underline hover:text-compass-green-dark transition-colors"
        >contact form</a
      >.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
